column12: Rotary turbo rocket
column13: A turbojet is combined with a co-axially integrated rotary rocket to form a propulsion system called a Rotary Turbo Rocket that can function as a turbojet, as an afterburning turbojet, as an Air Turbo Rocket, or as a rotary rocket. The Rotary Turbo Rocket can operate in any of these propulsion modes singularly, or in any combination of these propulsion modes, and can transition continuously or abruptly between operating modes. The Rotary Turbo Rocket can span the zero to orbital flight velocity speed range and/or operate continuously as it transitions from atmospheric to space flight by transitioning between operating modes.
column15: BOSSARD JOHN

column12: Improvements in or relating to Electro-despositing Devices.
column13: 17,092. Bossard, J. July 20. Cells; electrodes ; electrolytes, agitating.-An annular vessel, formed of sides 1, 2 and bottom 3, is supported upon trestles 4, while in the open space in the centre is supported, by a foot box 23 and traces 24, an upright shaft 29 which receives a slow rotary motion by means of a worm and worm-wheel 41, 40, shaft 43, ratchet-wheel 45, and driving-pawl 47. The pawl receives motion from a shaft 50 by means of a crank 48, adjustable link 44, and counterpoised rocking arm 46 to which the pawl is attached. The shaft 29 supports and carries around the curved arms 31, at the ends of which is a circular rigid carrier 35 having a metal band 36 on its outer side with notches 38. Engaging with these notches are hooks for suspending the articles to be plated in the bath, and also hooks carrying oilers at their lower ends to oil slightly the outer edge of the cathode ring 15, against which rest the hooks carrying the articles to be coated. The cathode ring is carried by brackets 13, and is connected to the negative pole of the dynamo by a wire 16. The anode plates 10 are supported in the electrolyte by carriers 5 connected to metal bands 8, 9 which are joined together by a metal strap 11, and also connected, when desired, to the positive pole of the dynamo. To cause the plating to be uniform on the articles, they are partly rotated, while being carried around the annular vat, by curved arms or clamps 68 supported on the cathode ring 15. By this double movement also the electrolyte is agitated. The operator standing at any point of the circumference of the vat can, without moving, remove all the articles from the vat and re-charge it with fresh articles. Two concentric cathode rings may be used, one on each side of the carrier, in which case the connection to the negative pole may pass through the hollow standard supporting the carrier, or may be made by a trolley travelling on the top of the metal band 15.

column12: MULTI-MODE COMBINED CYCLE PROPULSION ENGINE
column13: A turbojet engine capable of operation in an Air Turbo Rocket (ATR) mode includes a compressor, a rotatable turbine wheel comprising turbine blades, a non-rotating guide vane ring comprising guide vanes, a turbine shaft configured to power said compressor, a combustor, a gas generator, and a main combustor. The main combustor is configured to combust hot, fuel rich gas from the gas generator in air compressed by the compressor. Hot, fuel rich gas from the gas generator is directed towards the turbine blades by a directing means.

column12: Selectable delay pulse generator
column13: A programmable pulse generator having a clock signal delay chain, multiplexer, and reduced voltage charge circuit. The clock delay chain comprises a plurality of propagated delays, coupled to the multiplexer. The multiplexer selects a particular clock delay signal from a plurality of delay chain taps. The multiplexer is driven by a tap select register coupled to a state machine. The state machine controls the programmable pulse output, encoding the data by varying the pulse width and delay between pulses. The delay of pulse outputs from the multiplexer are reduced by coupling a reduced voltage pre-charge circuit to the multiplexer.

column12: VEHICLE BODY COUPLING
column13: A vehicle having front and rear body units rotatably connected by a body coupling for rotational movement about an axis parallel to the longitudinal axis of the vehicle. The coupling includes a hollow male member carried on the rear wall of the front body unit and extends through a sleeve carried on the front wall of the rear body with each being rigidly connected to their respective body walls by mounting plates. A plurality of bolt members extend outwardly from the inner peripheral surface of the hollow male member and extend through an end plate adapted to limit longitudinal movement of the sleeve on the male member. Wear plates are provided between the adjacent front and rear body walls and the end plate may be tightened against the sleeve as it is appropriate to compensate for wear on the wear plates.

column12: VEHICLE REAR WHEEL DRIVE ASSEMBLY
column13: A vehicle having front and rear body sections rotatably interconnected along the longitudinal axis of the body sections. An engine is located in the front body section and a drive shaft extends through the coupling between the body sections through the compartment of the rear body section and to a gear box on a rear axle located entirely outside of the compartment of the rear body section. The rear axle is supported by frame members extending rearwardly from the rear body section. A wall extends horizontally over the rear axle and provides a seat for the compartment in the rear body section. A propeller may be connected to a drive shaft extending rearwardly from the gear box on the rear axle.

column12: VEHICLE FRONT WHEEL DRIVE ASSEMBLY
column13: A drive assembly for a front wheel drive vehicle wherein a gear box is connected by a drive shaft and in turn provides driven shafts extending in opposite directions for connection with separate clutches which in turn are connected to the respective front wheels. Each of the clutches includes a pair of jaw portions semicylindrical in shape when in engagement with each other form a cylindrical drive member. Each of the jaw members are keyed to separate shafts for rotation therewith and an actuating lever is connected to a yoke in turn connected to one of the jaw members for sliding it along its shaft into and out of engagement with the other axially stationary jaw.

column12: Detection of water entrapped in electronic components
column13: The accuracy of measurements made to determine the extent of water vapor trapped upon encapsulation of an electronic device is significantly enhanced by carefully controlling the measurement technique employed. In particular, the encapsulant is generally punctured and the water vapor thus released is monitored. It has been found that to obtain an accurate measurement of the magnitude of the water vapor released, this measurement must be made within 0.1 second of the time of encapsulant punctured and released into a glass system. By using an absorption technique with suitable electronics, this time requirement is fulfilled and significantly more accurate quantitative measurements of entrapped water vapor are obtained.

column12: Vernier circuit for fine control of sample time
column13: A vernier time shifting circuit 100 is used for fine-tuning capture of a clock signal and/or a data signal to compensate for fluctuations produced by the system or other variations within non-time invariant parts of the chip. Other variations can include process, temperature, or voltage differences. The vernier sample time shifting circuit 100 allows shifting the signal in small steps to allow for optimal sampling. Various amounts of delay of the time-shifted signal are available at a plurality of output delay taps 113.
column15: FAGAN JOHN L BOSSARD MARK A CO

column12: DUAL PHASE PULSE MODULATION ENCODER CIRCUIT
column13: An dual phase pulse modulation (DPPM) encoder circuit (Fig. 3) converts data (11) into a series of high and low signal pulses (33; Fig. 2B), each of whose time durations or pulse widths represents a group of M data bits, with the alternating high and low pulses representing successive groups. The encoder circuit may include a set of parallel-in, serial-out shift registers (13A, 13B) that subdivide received data words into the M-bit groups, a state machine (19) that specifies the pulse durations for each received group, e.g., by incrementing a state (STATE (i)) that indicates selected signal pulse transition (TAP _ SELECT ⏧45:0]) times, a system clock delay chain (27) with multiple taps (T2 T92), a multiplexer (25) controlled (23) by the state machine for successively selecting different taps, and a toggle flip-flop (31) that is clocked by the multiplexer output (TAP_POINT, 29) .

column12: METHOD FOR COMMUNICATING IN A NETWORK, A SECONDARY STATION AND A SYSTEM THEREFOR
column13: The present invention relates to a method for communicating in a network, comprising a) a secondary station preparing the transmission to a primary station of a message comprising a report and a data field for containing data in an allocated resource, and b) the secondary station setting at least one transmission parameter of the message at a first level of reliability if the size of the allocated resource is bigger than the size of the message, and else setting at least one transmission parameter at second level of reliability being lower than the first level of reliability, c) the secondary station transmitting the message to the primary station.

column12: APPARATUS AND METHODS FOR INSPECTING DAMAGE INTENSITY
column13: An inspection apparatus including a light source, a sample holding stage, an image capture device, positioned to receive light from the light source after the light has interacted with a sample on the sample holding stage, and a damage metric. The damage metric includes two or more damage levels, and is a function of light in a test image. Further, the damage metric may correlate to visual observation so that an inspection apparatus may mimic how users of devices will perceive damage to the devices. The damage metric may be adjusted to account for different damage types, for example, abrasion and scratch damage.

column12: Facility Wide Mixed Mail Sorting and/or Sequencing System and Components and Methods Thereof
column13: The invention generally relates to a facility wide sorting and/or sequencing system for improving product processing operations and, more particularly, to a facility wide system and related functionality for simultaneously sorting and sequencing mixed mail pieces such as, for example, flats and letter mail pieces. The flats and letter mail pieces are placed in frames so that all types of mail pieces can be sorted and/or sequenced simultaneously through merging and diverting a stream of filled trays into and out of different streams at a full or substantially full transport speed.

column12: Process for preparing enantiomer of (1R, 4S)- or (1S, 4R)-1-amino-4-(hydroxymethyl)-2-cyclopentene derivative and (1R, 4S)-N-butyryl-1-amino-4-(hydroxymethyl)-2-cyclopentene enantiomer
column13: In the present invention, there is disclosed a process for preparing enantiomer of (1R, 4S)- or (1S, 4R)-1-amino-4-(hydroxymethyl)-2-cyclopentene derivative of the general formulae XVI, XVII wherein the preparation process is characterized in that in the first stage there is converted cyclopentene derivative of the general formula V to (1R,4S)- or (1S, 4R)-1-amino-4-(hydroxymethyl)-2-cyclopentene of the general formulae VI, VII using a microorganism being able to use cyclopentene derivative of the general formula V as the only source of nitrogen, carbon or carbon and nitrogen by means of N-acetyl-aminoalcohol hydrolase or by means of penicillin G acylase, and in the second stage the (1R,4S)- or (1S, 4R)-1-amino-4-(hydroxymethyl)-2-cyclopentene obtained in the first stage is then acylated to a compound of the general formula XVI or XVII. There is also disclosed (1R,4S)-N-butyryl-1-amino-4-(hydroxymethyl)-2-cyclopentene enantiomer of the general formula XVIII with more than 0 percent of enantiomeric excess.

column13: In the present invention, there is disclosed a process for preparing (1S,4R)- and/or (1R,4S)-4-(2-amino-6-chloro-9H-purin-9-yl)-2-cyclopentene-1-methanol of the general formulae I and II respectively or their salts comprising: (i) acylating (plus or minus)-2-azabicyclo (2.2.1) hept-5-en-3-one of the general formula III to obtain (plus or minus)-2-azabicyclo (2.2.1) hept-5-en-3-one derivative of the general formula IV; (ii) reducing the obtained derivative of the general formula IV to a 1-amino-4-(hydroxymethyl)-2-cyclopentene derivative of the general formula V; (iii) converting the derivative of the general formula V into (1R,4S)- or (1S,4R)-1-amino-4-(hydroxymethyl)-2-cyclopentene of the general formulae VI or VII respectively, using a biotechnological process; (iv) converting the compound obtained in the previous step by N-(2-amino-4,6-dichloropyrimidin-5-yl)-formamide of the general formula VIII to (1S,4R)- or (1R,4S)-4-[(2-amino-6-chlor-5-formamido-4-pyrimidinyl)-amino]-2-cyclo-pentene-1-methanol of the general formulae IX or X and (v) cyclising the obtained (1S,4R)- or (1R,4S)-4-((2-amino-6-chloro-5-formamido-4-pyrimidinyl)-amino)-2-cyclo pentene-1-methanol to the final product of the general formulae I or II.

column12: PROCESS FOR PRODUCING (15,4R)- OR (1R,4S)-4-[(2-AMINO-6-CHLORO-9H-PURIN)-9-YL]-2-CYCLOPENTENE-1-METHANOL
column13: A találmány tárgyát eljárás képezi az (I) vagy (II) képletű (1S,4R)-vagy (1R,4S)-4-(2-aminő-6-klór-9H-pűrin-9-il)-2-ciklőpentén-1-metanőlelőállítására. Ezen vegyületeket őly módőn állítják elő, hőgy (+)-2-azabiciklő[2.2.1]hept-5-én-3-őnt (IV) általánős képletű (+)-2-azabiciklő[2.2.1]-hept-5-én-3-őn-származékká acilezik, ahől aképletben R1 jelentése 1-4 szénatőmős alkil-, 1-4 szénatőmős alkőxi-,aril- vagy aril-őxi-csőpőrt; - majd a kapőtt vegyületet (V) általánősképletű ciklőpenténszármazékká redűkálják; - majd a kapőttvegyületeket egy N-acetilaminő-alkőhől-hidrőláz hatású enzimmikrőőrganizműsának segítségével vagy egy penicillin G-acilázsegítségével (VI) vagy (VII) képletű vegyületté alakítják; - majd akapőtt vegyületetet N-(2-aminő-4,6-diklór-pirimidin)-5-il-főrmamiddal(1S,4R)- vagy (1R,4S)-4-[(2-aminő-6-klór-5-főrmamidő-4-pirimidinil)-aminő]-2-ciklőpentén-1-metanőllá alakítják; - majd az így kapőttvegyületeket (I) vagy (II) képletű vegyületekké ciklizálják. Atalálmány szerinti eljárással kapőtt vegyületek közbenső termékként 2-aminő-pűrin-nűkleőzidők előállításáhőz alkalmazhatók. ŕ

column12: Process for preparing racemic or optically active 4-(hydroxymethyl)-2-cyclopentene derivative
column13: In the present invention, there is disclosed a process for preparing racemic or optically active 4-(hydroxymethyl)-2-cyclopentene derivative of the general formula wherein the preparation process comprises acylating a cyclopentene-4-carboxylic acid of the general formula XIV in the form of a racemate or one optically active isomer thereof with a halide of the carboxylic acid of the general formula XI to a racemic or optically active derivative of the cyclopentene-4-carboxylic acid of the general formula XV, in a first preparation stage, while in the second preparation stage said derivative obtained in the first stage is then reduced to a required product of the general formula XIII.

column12: Process for the preparation of a (1R, 4S)- or (1S, 4R)-1-amino-4- (hydroxymethyl)-2-cyclopentene derivative and an enantiomer of a (1R,4S)-N-butyryl-1-amino-4-(hydroxymethyl)-2-cyclopenten
column13: The present invention relates to a process for the preparation of an enantiomer of a (1R, 4S)- or (1S, 4R)-1-amino- 4-(hydroxymethyl)-2-cyclopentene derivative of the general formulae (I) and (II), wherein R1 is a C1-4-alkyl, a C1-4-alkoxy, an aryl, or an aryloxy at which in the first stage a 1-amino-4-(hydroxymethyl)-2-cyclopentene derivative of the general formula (IV), wherein R1 is a C1-4-alkyl, an aryl, or an aryloxy is converted using a microorganism which is able to utilize a cyclopeptide derivative of the general formula (IV) as sole nitrogen source, as sole carbon source or as sole carbon and nitrogen source, an enzyme having N-acetylamino-alcohol hydrolase activity or a penicillin G acylase into the (1R, 4S)- or (1S, 4R)-1-amino-4-(hyroxymethyl)-2-cyclopentene of the general formula (V) or (VI) and the latter is then acylated in the second stage to give the compounds of the formula (I) or (II). Enantiomer of (1R, 4S)-N-butyryl-1-amino-4-(hydroxymethyl)-2- cyclopentene of the formula (III).

column12: Process for the preparation of (1S,4R)- or (1R,4S)-4-(2-amino-6- chloro-9H-purin-9-yl)-2-cyclo-pentene-1-methanol
column13: Process for the preparation of (1S,4R)- or (1R,4S)-4-(2- amino-6-chloro-9H-purin-9-yl)-2-cyclo-pentene-1-methanol of the formulae (I) and (II) is described. This entails in the first stage (+/-)-2-aza-bicyclo[2.2.1]hept-5-en-3-one of the formula (III) being acylated to give a (+/-)-2-azabicyclo[2.2.1]hept-5- en-3-one derivative of the general formula (IV) in which R1 denotes -(C1-C4)alkyl, -(C1-C4)alkoxy, aryl or aryloxy, the latter being reduced in the second stage to give a cyclopentene derivative of the general formula (V) in which R1 has the stated meaning, the latter then being converted in the third stage biotechnologically into the (1R,4S)- or (1S,4R)-1-amino-4- (hydroxymethyl)-2-cyclopentene of the formula (VI, VII) the latter being converted in the fourth stage with N-(2-amino-4,6- dichloro-5-pyrimidinyl)formamide of the formula (VIII) into the (1S,4R)- or (1R,4S)-4-[(2-amino-6-chloro-5-formamido-4- pyrimidinyl)amino]-2-cyclopentene-1-methanol of the formulae (IX, X) and the latter being cyclized in the fifth stage in a known manner to the final product of the formula (I) or (II).

column12: Process for the preparation of a racemic or optically active 4-(hydroxymethyl)-2-cyclopentene derivative and racemic N-butyryl-1-amino-4-(hydroxymethyl)-2-cyclopentene
column13: The present invention relates to a process for the preparation of a racemic or optically active 4-(hydroxymethyl)-2- cyclopentene derivative of the formula (I) in which the group R1 is a C1-4-alkyl, a C1-4-alkoxy, an aryl, or an aryloxy at which in the first stage a cyclopentene-4-carboxylic acid of the formula (II) in the form of the racemate or one of its optically active isomers, is acylated with a carbonyl halide of the general formula (III) in which the group R1 is a C1-4-alkyl, a C1-4-alkoxy, an aryl, or an aryloxy and in which X is a halogen, which is selected from the group consisting of F, Cl, Br, or I, to give a racemic or optically active cyclopentene-4- carboxylic acid derivatives of the general formula (IV) and the latter is reduced in the second stage to give the required product of the formula (I). Enantiomer of (1R, 4S)-N-butyryl-1- amino-4-(hydroxymethyl)-2-cyclopentene.

column12: PROCESS FOR PREPARING (1S, 4R)- OR (1R, 4S)-4-(2-AMINO-6-CHLORO-9H-PURINE-9-YL)-2-CYCLOPENTENE-1-METHANOL
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a process for preparing an enantiomer of a cyclopentene derivative of formula XVI or XVII (wherein R1 is 1-4C alkyl, 1-4C alkoxy, aryl, or aryloxy), which is an intermediate for synthesizing (1S, 4R)- or (1R, 4S)-4-(2-amino-6-chloro-9H-purine-9-yl)-2-cyclopentene-1-methanol easily at a low cost and economically.

SOLUTION: In the process for preparing an enantiomer of a cyclopentene derivative, the cyclopentene derivative is converted into (1S, 4R)- or (1R, 4S)-1-amino-4-(hydroxymethyl)-2-cyclopentene by using a microorganism capable of utilizing a racemic cyclopentene derivative as a sole nitrogen source and/or a sole carbon source or by using an enzyme having N-acetylamino alcohol hydrolase activity or the like, and then is cyclized.

column12: PROCESS FOR PREPARATION OF (1S, 4R)-OR (1R, 4S)-4-(2-AMINO-6-CHLORO-9H-PURINE-9-YL)-2-CYCLOPENTENE-1-METHANOL
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a process for preparation of a 4-(hydroxymethyl)-2-cyclopentene derivative useful for a medicinal intermediate.

SOLUTION: The process for preparation of a 4-(hydroxymethyl)-2-cyclopentene derivative (XIII) represented by formula XIII includes the first stage wherein one of a racemic substance or an optically active isomer of 4-amino-2-cyclopentene carboxylic acid is acylated with a carboxylic acid halide to prepare a 4-acylamino-2-cyclopentene carboxylic acid derivative and the second stage wherein the acylamino-2-cyclopentene carboxylic acid derivative is reduced. In the formula, R1is 1-4C alkyl, etc.

column12: Multistep process for the preparation of (1S,4R)- and/or (1R,4S)-4-(2-Amino-6-Chlor-9-H-purin-9-yl)-2-cyclopentene-1-methanol
column13:
Beschrieben wird ein neues Verfahren zur Herstellung von (1S,4R)- oder (1R,4S)-4-(2-amino-6-chlor-9-H-purin-9-yl)-2-cyclopenten-1-methanol der Formeln
  Dabei wird in der ersten Stufe (±)-2-Azabicyclo[2.2.1]hept-5-en-3-on der Formel
   zu einem (±)-2-Azabicyclo[2.2.1]hept-5-en-3-on-derivat der allgemeinen Formel
   worin R 1  C 1-4 -Alkyl, C 1-4 -Alkoxy, Aryl oder Aryloxy bedeutet, acyliert, dieses in der zweiten Stufe zu einem Cyclopentenderivat der allgemeinen Formel
   worin R 1  die genannte Bedeutung hat, reduziert, dieses dann in der dritten Stufe biotechnologisch in das (1R,4S)- oder (1S,4R)-1-amino-4-(hydroxymethyl)-2-cyclopenten gemäss der Formel   umsetzt, dieses in der vierten Stufe mit N-(2-amino-4,6-dichlorpyrimidin)-5-yl)formamid der Formel
   ins (1S,4R)- oder (1R,4S)-4-[(2-amino-6-chlor-5-formamido-4-pyrimidinyl)-amino]-2-cyclopenten-1-methanol der Formeln
   überführt und letzteres in der fünften Stufe aufbekannte Weise zum Endprodukt gemäss Formel I oder II cyclisiert.

column12: Facility wide mixed mail sorting and/or sequencing system and components and methods thereof
column13: The invention generally relates to a facility wide sorting and/or sequencing system for improving product processing operations and, more particularly, to a facility wide system and related functionality for simultaneously sorting and sequencing mixed mail pieces such as, for example, flats and letter mail pieces. The flats and letter mail pieces are placed in frames so that all types of mail pieces can be sorted and/or sequenced simultaneously through merging and diverting a stream of filled trays into and out of different streams at a full or substantially full transport speed.

column12: PRODUCTION OF (1S,4R)-OR(1R,4S)-4-(2-AMINO-6-CHLORO9H-PURIN-9-YL)-2-CYCLOPENTENE-1-METHANOL
column13: PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To produce the subject compound useful as an intermediate, etc., for producing a 2-aminopurine nucleoside at a low cost by acylating 2- azabicyclo-hept-5-en-3-ones, reducing the resultant compounds and then reacting the obtained product with a specific microorganism, etc. SOLUTION: A (±)-2-azabicyclo[2.2.1]hept-5-en-3-one represented by formula I is acylated to provide an N-acylated derivative represented by formula II (R<1> is a 1-4C alkyl, a 1-4C alkoxy, an aryl or an aryloxy), which is then reduced to afford a cyclopentene derivative represented by formula III. The resultant cyclopentene derivative represented by formula III is subsequently reacted with a microorganism capable of assimilating the compound as only one nitrogen source, as only one carbon source or as the only one nitrogen source and the only one carbon source or an Nacetylaminoalcohol hydrolase, etc., to provide an optically active amino derivative, which is then reacted with an N-(2- amino-4,6dichloro-5-pyridinyl)formamide represented by formula IV and further cyclized to thereby afford the objective compound represented by formula V.

column12: Process for the preparation of 1-amino-4-(hydroxymethyl)-2-cyclopentene derivatives
column13:
Beschrieben wird ein Verfahren zur Herstellung eines racemischen oder optisch aktiven 4-(Hydroxymethyl)-2-cyclopentenderivats der allgemeinen Formel
   worin R 1  C 1-4 -Alkyl, C 1-4 -Alkoxy, Aryl oder Aryloxy bedeutet. Bei diesem Verfahren wird ein Cyclopenten-4-carbonsäure der Formel
   in Form des Racemats oder eines seiner optisch aktiven Isomeren mit einem Carbonsäurehalogenid der allgemeinen Formel
   worin R 1  die genannte Bedeutung hat und X ein Halogenatom bedeutet, zu einem racemischen oder optisch aktiven Cyclopenten-4-carbonsäurederivat der allgemeinen Formel
   acyliert und dieses zum gewünschten Produkt gemäss Formel XIII reduziert.

column12: Facility Wide Mixed Mail Sorting and/or Sequencing System and Components and Methods Thereof
column13: The invention generally relates to a facility wide sorting and/or sequencing system for improving product processing operations and, more particularly, to a facility wide system and related functionality for simultaneously sorting and sequencing mixed mail pieces such as, for example, flats and letter mail pieces. The flats and letter mail pieces are placed in frames so that all types of mail pieces can be sorted and/or sequenced simultaneously through merging and diverting a stream of filled trays into and out of different streams at a full or substantially full transport speed.
